  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">This is a rough draft of a letter by Maria Weston Chapman to Nathaniel B. Borden acknowledging a donation of $10 for the Liberty Bell. Chapman thanks Borden for informing her &quot;of the state of feeling &amp; action on the cause in congress.&quot; She reflects on the measures proposed by &quot;men of doubtful honesty.&quot; She cites the case of Charles Turner Torrey, who is reported as &quot;in prison awaiting his trial as an incendiary.&quot; Chapman entreats Borden&apos;s good offices in Torrey&apos;s aid. Although Torrey has been &quot;an enemy to the abolitionists...it matters not to them...in whose person the rights of civilization are violated.&quot;</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">This letter is written on the blank pages and margins of a circular (flier) advertising dancing and waltzing lessons at Mrs. Hunt&apos;s school of dance.</subfield>
  </datafield>
